.TH "kvm_s390_gisc_register" 9 "kvm_s390_gisc_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kvm_s390_gisc_register \- register a guest ISC
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" kvm_s390_gisc_register
.BI "(struct kvm *kvm "  ","
.BI "u32 gisc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "kvm" 12
the kernel vm to work with
.IP "gisc" 12
the guest interruption sub class to register
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The function extends the vm specific alert mask to use.
The effective IAM mask in the GISA is updated as well
in case the GISA is not part of the GIB alert list.
It will be updated latest when the IAM gets restored
by \fBgisa_get_ipm_or_restore_iam\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
the nonspecific ISC (NISC) the gib alert mechanism
has registered with the channel subsystem.
-ENODEV in case the vm uses no GISA
-ERANGE in case the guest ISC is invalid
